{"submission_id":"sub_718dbab4b1cf69eb","run_id":"2026-06-20T12-42-56-610Z_1885472-db60d070_ingest_meeting-doc-124141","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T13:56:33.368Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:718dbab4b1cf69ebc2590c67a7c0e99f7019ad33f8fed066a9e6a745854181ab","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_124141","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_mdoc124141_ytd_passenger_revenue_variance","label":"YTD Passenger Revenue Variance Explanation","raw_text":"MNR, the LIRR, and MTA Bus were favorable by $27.4M, $9.9M, and $3.4M, respectively, mainly due to higher ridership. These results were partially offset by an unfavorable variance of ($9.0M) at NYCT, mainly due to lower Bus ridership, partially offset by higher Subway ridership.","payload":{"claim_text":"MNR, the LIRR, and MTA Bus were favorable by $27.4M, $9.9M, and $3.4M, respectively, mainly due to higher ridership. These results were partially offset by an unfavorable variance of ($9.0M) at NYCT, mainly due to lower Bus ridership, partially offset by higher Subway ridership.","change_type":"mixed","extra_fields":{"subject":"Passenger Revenue","period":"September 2023 year-to-date"},"change_type_normalized":{"raw_text":"mixed","normalized_value":"mixed"}},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_124141","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_124141#p003_c0005","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_124141/blocks.jsonl","page_number":3,"block_id":"p003_c0005","text_sha256":"sha256:a1413cb9247863736980a17d6dbb8020af8ccf739898a1dec2dba22c2189d0c7","text_source":"raw_text","source_quote":"MNR, the LIRR, and MTA Bus were favorable by $27.4M, $9.9M, and $3.4M, respectively, mainly due to higher ridership. These results were partially offset by an unfavorable variance of ($9.0M) at NYCT, mainly due to lower Bus ridership, partially offset by higher Subway ridership."}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_24074d93c8789751","run_id":"2026-06-20T12-42-56-610Z_1885472-db60d070_ingest_meeting-doc-124141","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T13:56:58.428Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:24074d93c8789751cc441b79d2db723fbd1097ccc7fc8db0173c0ba2a53b2a5c","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_124141","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_mdoc124141_ytd_subsidies_variance","label":"YTD Subsidies Unfavorable Variance - PMT Evaluation","raw_text":"The unfavorable variances mainly reflected unfavorable results for PMT of $110.5M, this is being evaluated to ascertain if the variance is real or if it reflects issues arising from the implementation of new tax rates for large employers in NYC that became effective in July 2023.","payload":{"claim_text":"The unfavorable variances mainly reflected unfavorable results for PMT of $110.5M, this is being evaluated to ascertain if the variance is real or if it reflects issues arising from the implementation of new tax rates for large employers in NYC that became effective in July 2023.","change_type":"unfavorable","extra_fields":{"subject":"Subsidies","period":"September 2023 year-to-date","note":"PMT variance of $110.5M being evaluated for root cause"},"change_type_normalized":{"raw_text":"unfavorable","normalized_value":"unfavorable"}},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_124141","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_124141#p007_c0007","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_124141/blocks.jsonl","page_number":7,"block_id":"p007_c0007","text_sha256":"sha256:bff42b07240e32e75cc7491b3b5b367148360a717bbac3a59b0c5a395982fce4","text_source":"raw_text","source_quote":"The unfavorable variances mainly reflected unfavorable results for PMT of $110.5M, this is being evaluated to ascertain if the variance is real or if it reflects issues arising from the implementation of new tax rates for large employers in NYC that became effective in July 2023."}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_6dea286f84ac6656","run_id":"2026-06-20T12-42-56-610Z_1885472-db60d070_ingest_meeting-doc-124141","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T13:57:22.735Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:6dea286f84ac66560e10a10ee5270b9ad9356d67e562a72404688bff9f192e4a","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_124141","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_mdoc124141_ytd_debt_service_favorable","label":"YTD Debt Service Favorable Variance","raw_text":"Debt Service expenses were $2,056.9 million, which was $29.3 million or 1.4% favorable due to investment income, timing related to debt issuance, and refunding savings; approximately $6 million of the YTD positive variance is expected to be reversed in October.","payload":{"claim_text":"Debt Service expenses were $2,056.9 million, which was $29.3 million or 1.4% favorable due to investment income, timing related to debt issuance, and refunding savings; approximately $6 million of the YTD positive variance is expected to be reversed in October.","change_type":"favorable","extra_fields":{"subject":"Debt Service","period":"September 2023 year-to-date"},"change_type_normalized":{"raw_text":"favorable","normalized_value":"favorable"}},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_124141","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_124141#p007_c0009","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_124141/blocks.jsonl","page_number":7,"block_id":"p007_c0009","text_sha256":"sha256:e71b4aaf37369152ea412adb7842f4842e65edb6ee01de2876167012a7d6ed5c","text_source":"raw_text","source_quote":"Debt Service expenses were $2,056.9 million, which was $29.3 million or 1.4% favorable due to investment income, timing related to debt issuance, and refunding savings; approximately $6 million of the YTD positive variance is expected to be reversed in October."}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
